This is a standalone server for networking game play with gltron.
Usage: /opt/cvs/gltron/server/server [-h] [-f <conffile>]
 
-f      set config file path ( default server.conf )
-h      this help

Config file:
The default config file is server.conf in the same directory as the server.
Comments are line starting with a #.
Four variables need to be set:
port: port is the port on which server listenning to incomming connection.
default is 23460.

passwd: is the passwd used to connect to a masterserver ( tracker ).

tracker: is the IP address of the tracker. If set to NO, server won't connect to the tracker. WARNING: tracker address should be the address from internet interface if server and tracker are on the same machine. Using localhost is a bad idea because tracker will show 127.0.0.1 in server list.

tport: is the port to connect to the tracker. default is 23470.

